review_blob: 12 oz. 2007 pours a dark cloudy red with almost no head. This has become one of my favorite weekly purchases. even stored one away til 2008.
12oz. bottle pours a dark reddish brown with a small amount of head. Another strong brew from Avery.
bottle pours a dark brown with a reddish hue, and almost no head. Not a bad brew at all.
beer_name: Left Hand Wake Up Dead Imperial Stout

review_blob: 750ml bottle corked and caged, pours a redish copper color with a rediculous khaki head. Sweet taste, but I think this is the first unibroue brew where I didnt notice any floaters.
22oz bottle pours a cloudy copper color with  a bubbly thin white head. Another excellent Avery brew and my first Imperial/Double IPA.
beer_name: Avery The Maharaja Imperial India Pale Ale

review_blob: 12oz bottle batch#4 pours a deep red-purple color with almost no head to speak of. This got a lot of blood in my alcohol system fast. The Beast name fits this beer well. To sweet for my taste, but good damn that beer packs a punch.
beer_name: Avery The Beast Grand Cru Ale

review_blob: 650ml bottle pours a slightly hazy orangish-gold color with a decent head. fruity with a 9% dry alcohol taste. Another fine Avery brew, but I think I like the collaboration a little better.
22oz bottle pours a deep burgundy color, with a medium tan head. The 9.2%abv is well hidden. Another damn good beer from Avery Brew Comp.
12oz bottle pours a hazy dark burgundy color, with a minamal amount of tan head. There was not as much of an alcohol warmth as I would expect from a 10.5% brew. Another good Flying Dog beer.
beer_name: Flying Dog Horn Dog Barley Wine

review_blob: 750ml bottle pours a deep dark red, with a nice thick tan head, that disappated very slowly. This was my first brew from Ommegang, and I was plesently suprised how much I liked it. Next up, Three Philosophers.
Big bottle pours a dark brown with a reddish hue, and a thick tan head. Another damn fine beer from Unibroue.
22oz bottle that pours a dark copper color with a thick tan head. 10% alcohol that goes down smooth at 4$. My new favorite.
12oz bottle pours a clear golden color with a little white head. This is my favorite pilsner, because it doesnt taste much like a pilsner.

beer_brewer_name: Schneider Weisse G. Schneider & Sohn GmbH
review_blob: 16.9oz bottle pours a dark brown with a shade of purple. It also had a thick light tan head. This was a fuckin tasty beer that I will probably buy again.
11.2oz bottle pours a cloudy piss color, a thin white head and some floaters. Overall this is a damn good beer.
1pint 0.9oz. bottle pours a dark amber orange head, with a good light tan head. Overall it was a descent beer for the price, but I wish it was a little stronger.
beer_name: Black Sheep Monty Pythons Holy Grail (Bottle)

Batch #86

10$ for a 24 pack, aint notin wrong wit dat.

12 oz. bottle pours a clear dark goldish color. Citrus smell and taste. This was a unique IPA that I will probably get again.
Hooray beer! I like Red Stripe because, whenever I stand next to one of those ugly little red headed stepchildren, it makes me look better. Oh yeah, and I cant dance without it.

I was exited to finally try this beer. So exited I figured fuck the orange I dont need it. I grabbed my frosty Trappist glass, and the rest was disappointment. I dont get why so many people think its great. Its only descent one at a time.

Optimator pours a dark brown with almost no head. It hides its 7.2% a lot better than Arrogant Bastards 7.2%. This was pretty tasty but not as good as Salvator.
Chimay Red pours an amber color with a trademark Chimay thick white head. You can never go wrong with a Chimay.
Chimay White pours a hazy orangish gold color with an impressive head. You can never go wrong with a Chimay, no matter the color.
Hop Devil pours a nice dark amber color with a nice white head, that slowly diminishes. Another example of why Victory is one of my favorite brewers.
Addison,TX Jeramiah Red on tap pours a red amber color with a thin diminishing head. This is my favorite of the BJs beer linup.
Twin sisters pours an orangish copper color, with a lasting white head. I didnt like the bits of yeast in this beer, but other than that I thought it was a good beer.
beer_name: Left Hand Twin Sisters Double IPA

review_blob: Sawtooth Ale pours a cloudy copper color, with a light white head with a little bit of lacing. This was my first ESB and I rather enjoyed it.
This milk stout pours a dark brown color with a medium tan head. This was my first milk stout, but Id like to try others. Overall I enjoyed my first milk stout.
Jackman Pale Ale pours a clear orangish copper color with a thick white head. Overall its an above average american pale ale.
Black Jack porter pours such a dark brown that its almost black. It has a small amount of deminishing head, with a little bit of lacing. Overall its an OK porter.
Gotta love the head on this Belgian ale! Pours a bubbley golden color. I would recomend this beer.
Great beer for the price, especially when you can find it for the same price as generic domestic beer.
Newcastle is a classic good beer at a bar. I always figured it was a little stronger than 4.7%
This beer is extremely overratted and over priced! That being said, its still one of my favorites when its really cold, or if its 2$ you call it, its better than Bud.
XX pours a golden yellow with a thin white head. This is one of the few descent mexican beers. Great with mexican food.
Carta Blanca pours a clear golden color with thin white head. Its mexican beer so its pretty much overpriced mexican piss.
This beer pours a light amber color with a diminishing head and decent lacing. You can smell and taste the grapefruit. Its a decent beer from New Belgium brewing.
This Imp Stout pours such a dark brown that it is almost black with a thick white head with good lacing. Sweet chocolate, coffe, and roasted malts are the dominant tastes.
This was my first Stone beer, and it was excellent. It pours a dark amber with a thin khaki head. This is the strongest and best tasting strong ale ive come across.
Chimay Blue pours a dark cloudy amber color with a light brown vanishing head. This is the beer that got me into this site, and into quality beers.

I dont know why I love this beer, but i do. I think it tastes like mexican piss. But their is nothing like standing on a beach in Cancun or PV with a cold Corona with lime. over priced and over rated, but a centamental favorite.
